subSubSection.paragraph:
Advertisement call.
Description based on 129 calls recorded from two males (
Table 3
). The call (
Fig. 6h
) consists of single, pulsed notes given at a rate of 124–275 per minute. Note duration varies from 27–70 ms. Rise time varies from 37–80% of note duration. Notes are formed by 2–7 partly fused pulses emitted at a rate of 57–153 per second. The dominant frequency coincides with the fundamental harmonic at 495–1098 Hz. Notes have no frequency modulation or a modest frequency upsweep throughout their duration, varying from 0–560 Hz.
